text: Galyn Görg, pronounced George, also credited as Galyn Gorg, Galan Gorg and Gaylyn Görg (July 15, 1964 – July 14, 2020) was an American actress and dancer. She was best known for her role in the movies, RoboCop 2 as Angie, the Nuke addicted bad girl; on M.A.N.T.I.S., television's first black superhero program, as Lt. Maxwell and on the television show Twin Peaks as Nancy O'Reilly. She was born in Los Angeles. Görg died of cancer in Hawaii on July 14, 2020, the day before her 56th birthday. ==References== Category:1964 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Cancer deaths in Hawaii Category:American movie actors Category:American television actors Category:American dancers Category:Actors from Los Angeles
